The Sultan of Sokoto and President-General of the Nigerian Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs, Alhaji Saâ€™ad Abubakar III, has announced the commencement of the Holy month of Ramadan fast.  According to the Religious leader, the moon has been sighted in different locations in Nigeria and was confirmed by different committees both in the states and at the national level, signifying the commencement of the Ramadan fasting this Friday (today). He admonished Muslims to adhere to the social distancing announced by the Health Authorities while observing their worship to God.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Sultan also urged Muslims to use the Holy month of Ramadan to rededicate themselves and live peacefully with one another irrespective of tribal, political and religious differences.